426. In venimus and malum the final consonants should be dropped—malum is here an in- terjection apparently belonging to eonversational language and frequently met with in the comio writers. Even Cicero uses it occasionany, e. g. Off. 11 15, 13 quae te malum ratio in istam spem intimuit? ‘what the deuce could lead you to such a hope?’ Verr. 1 20, 54 quae malum est ista tanta audacia atque amen- tIa? It always expresses a strong degree of indignation and anger.
